  "text": "(e) Extent of mitochondrial tRNA localization Studies in trypanosomatids [CITATION_1] and Chlamydomonas [CITATION_2] ), which import all or nearly all of their mitochondrial tRNAs, revealed large variations between the extent of mitochondrial localization of individual tRNAs. In both organisms, these variations were not correlated with the cytosolic concentration of the tRNAs. This raises two questions: why is the extent of mitochondrial localization of different tRNAs so variable and how is it regulated?",
